# Auto-deploy on changes

When you finish implementing or fixing something in this repo:

1. Commit all intentional code changes (exclude secrets, `.env*`, and local preview/script artifacts unless the user asked for them).
2. Push to `origin master` to trigger the Vercel deploy.
3. Tell the user deployment was pushed — no need to wait for them to ask "deploy" separately.

Only skip auto-deploy when:
- The user explicitly says not to deploy or not to commit.
- There are no changes to commit.
- Push fails and needs user approval on the protected branch — retry once with approval, then report the blocker.

After push, briefly note what was deployed and the live URL: https://www.mlihrent.com
